  "name": "Ró Sálna",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>This broad-bladed sword, sometimes called the hand-and-a-half sword, has a longer grip so it can be held in one hand or used with two hands to provide extra slashing power.</p><p>This sword is a special model made for the Scarlet Blade. It was lovingly crafted by the Scarlet Blade's parent and enchanted with a minor effect keeping it pristine in all conditions.</p><p>It is crafted out of a special and rare material known only as soulsteel - a dark, nearly black metal with veins of silver - that is difficult to work due to its more volatile properties.</p><p>Soulsteel pulls at both the lifeforce of the living, and the energy that animates the undead, wielder and foe ailke. A skilled magical crafter can help attune this material to a particular user, usually someone who is a decent mage in their own right, so that it doesn't harm them.</p><p>A weapon crafted of this material deals 1 extra spirit damage. At 6th level, this damage is replaced by an @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.6llILJtsTPgtYXgx]{Astral} rune; this rune cannot be removed, and it deals 1d8 damage instead of 1d6 damage. At 14th level, this weapon automatically gains a @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.hebf5k3cd7LO6luX]{Astral (Greater)} rune instead. It is also able to affect incorporeal creatures as if it had the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.JQdwHECogcTzdd8R]{Ghost Touch} rune. However, creatures other than those attuned to this weapon cannot handle it without feeling a sense of unease, and the weapon pulling at their lifeforce. Incorporeal creatures cannot touch it without feeling great pain, dropping it immediately.</p>"
    },
